cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY

The paper discusses the impact of cognitive biases on decision-making in visual analytics, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The task of identifying misinformation from Twitter news accounts involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of coordinated multiple view design in the visual analytic system suggests a focus on information visualization (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the training of users, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it relates to educating users on how to avoid unintentional anchoring.
